\par }{\f4\cgrid0 2.}{\b\f4\cgrid0 \tab }{\f4\cgrid0 When the Terrain Window opens, }{\b\f4\cgrid0 Accept}{\f4\cgrid0  the first terrain that is offered.
\par 
\par 3.\tab Use the }{\b\f4\cgrid0 Build Road}{\f4\cgrid0  tool to create a single straight road that is approximately 50 tiles long.
\par 
\par 4.\tab Create residential, commercial, and industrial zones along the length of the road. The zones can be as large as you want, but they should extend at least 6 tiles on either side of the road.
\par 
\par 5.\tab Place power, power lines (if necessary), water, and water pipes in the city.
\par 
\par 6.\tab Select the }{\b\f4\cgrid0 Preferences }{\f4\cgrid0 option from the}{\b\f4\cgrid0  Change Settings & Exit }{\f4\cgrid0 Menu. Disable }{\b\f4\cgrid0 Disasters}{\f4\cgrid0 , then click on the checkmark to close the Preferences Window.
\par 
\par 7.\tab You will be using this city for several simulations, so }{\i\f4\cgrid0 before }{\f4\cgrid0 you run the simulation, save the city as 1RoadTown.
\par 
\par 8.\tab Click on the }{\b\f4\cgrid0 Run Simulation }{\f4\cgrid0 Button to start the simulation. Run the simulation for two years. Then pause it.
