\par }{\b\f4\fs28\cgrid0 Simulation 3: It's About Crime
\par }{\f4\fs24\cgrid0 
\par }{\b\f4\fs24\cgrid0 Objectives
\par }{\f4\cgrid0 
\par }\pard \fi-240\li720\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\f4\cgrid0 \bullet \tab To discover methods for reducing crime in a city.
\par 
\par }\pard \nowidctlpar\adjustright {\b\f4\fs24\cgrid0 The Activity
\par }{\f4\cgrid0 
\par In this simulation, students will run three simulations to observe the effects of police service on crime rates. First, students will load a starter town tha
t comes with one police station. They will run the simulation for a year and record the crime level at the end of the year. In the second simulation, students will repeat the simulation after adding a second police station. And in the third simulation, st
udents will use a second police station as well as a jail. They will then compare and contrast the results. Students will discover that adding police stations reduces crime in the city, and adding jails increasing the effectiveness of the police stations.

\par 
\par Have students perform the following actions:
\par 
\par }\pard \fi-360\li360\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\f4\cgrid0 1.\tab }{\b\f4\cgrid0 Simulation A:}{\f4\cgrid0  Start }{\i\f4\cgrid0 SimCity 3000}{\f4\cgrid0  and load Suburbia (a Starter Town that comes with the program).
\par 
\par 2.\tab Select the }{\b\f4\cgrid0 Preferences }{\f4\cgrid0 option from the}{\b\f4\cgrid0  Change Settings & Exit }{\f4\cgrid0 Menu. Disable }{\b\f4\cgrid0 Disasters}{\f4\cgrid0 , then click on the checkmark to close the Preferences Window.
\par 
\par 3.\tab Run the simulation for one year (Sim time), then click on the }{\b\f4\cgrid0 Pause Simulation}{\f4\cgrid0  button to pause the simulation.
\par 
\par 4.\tab Select the }{\b\f4\cgrid0 View Data}{\f4\cgrid0  option from the }{\b\f4\cgrid0 Adjust & Review}{\f4\cgrid0  Menu to open the View Data Window. Use the }{\b\f4\cgrid0 Graphs}{\f4\cgrid0 
 tool in the View Data Window to view the current crime level. Record this value on a separate piece of paper.
\par 
\par 5.\tab Select the }{\b\f4\cgrid0 View Data}{\f4\cgrid0  option from the }{\b\f4\cgrid0 Adjust & Review}{\f4\cgrid0  Menu to open the View Data Window. Click on the }{\b\f4\cgrid0 Crime Data Map }{\f4\cgrid0 button in the View Data}{\b\f4\cgrid0  }{
\f4\cgrid0 Window to view the level of crime in the city. Click on }{\b\f4\cgrid0 Use as Map}{\f4\cgrid0  to use the crime map as the Navigation Map.
\par 
\par 6.\tab Refer to the crime navigation map as you scroll around the city. In general, which types of areas have
 the heaviest crime rates? Is there any crime in the area protected by the police department? What would be a good location for a second police department? Why?
