\par 9.\tab Place a second police department in the location you selected in Step 6.
\par 
\par 10.\tab Run the simulation for one year, then click on the }{\b\f4\cgrid0 Pause Simulation}{\f4\cgrid0  button to pause the simulation.
\par 
\par 11.\tab Use the }{\b\f4\cgrid0 Graphs}{\f4\cgrid0  tool in the }{\b\f4\cgrid0 View Data}{\f4\cgrid0  Window to view the current crime level. Record this value on a separate piece of paper.
\par 
\par 12.\tab Do not save this city.
\par }\pard \nowidctlpar\adjustright {\f17\fs24\cgrid0 
\par }\pard \fi-360\li360\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\f4\cgrid0 13.\tab }{\b\f4\cgrid0 Simulation C: }{\f4\cgrid0 Reload Suburbia, and make sure the disaster preference is disabled.
\par 
\par 14.\tab Place a second police department in the same location you used in Simulation B. Then add a jail to the city.
\par 
\par 15.\tab Run the simulation for one year, then click on the }{\b\f4\cgrid0 Pause Simulation}{\f4\cgrid0  button to pause the simulation.
\par 
\par 16.\tab Use the }{\b\f4\cgrid0 Graphs}{\f4\cgrid0  tool in the }{\b\f4\cgrid0 View Data}{\f4\cgrid0  Window to view the current crime level. Record this value on a separate piece of paper. 
\par 
\par }\pard \nowidctlpar\adjustright {\b\f4\cgrid0 FOLLOW UP}{\b\f4\fs24\cgrid0 : }{\f4\cgrid0 Have the students use the information they recorded to answer the following questions
\par }\pard \fi-240\li240\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\f4\cgrid0 \bullet \tab Is the crime rate in Simulation B higher, lower, or about the same as the crime rate in Simulation A?
\par \bullet \tab Is the crime rate in Simulation C higher, lower, or about the same as the crime rate in Simulation B?
\par \bullet \tab Do jails increase the effectiveness of the police force? Explain your answer.
\par \bullet \tab If you added more police stations, so that the coverage area of the stations covered the whole city, you could effectively reduce the crime rate to zero. Do you think the same is true in a real city? Why or why not?
\par }\pard \nowidctlpar\adjustright {\f4\cgrid0 
